 postmodernity is not iconoclasm, but rather a radically iconic account of the visual and the arts that opens them to the invisible.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 15. Sep 2020) 0aPaintingxPhilosophy. 0aPerspective. 0aPhenomenology. 0aVisual perception. 7aART / Techniques / Painting.2bisacsh1 aSmith, James K. A.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013z978311070420440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978150360271740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781503602717423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/cover/covers/9781503602717.jpg  a978-3-11-070420-4  SUP Backlist eBook-Package 2000-2013c2000d2013  aGBV-deGruyter-alles